[4] Cholera - Tanzania (Tanga Region)
Date: Mon 2 Nov 2015
Source: All Africa [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201511021730.html


The cholera outbreak has spread to Handeni District in Tanga Region, killing 6 people. Residents of the district are warned to take immediate precautionary steps to prevent the bacterial disease from spreading further. According to experts, the cause of the outbreak is mainly due to people drinking un-boiled water and using improper pit latrines.

Head of the health department at the Handeni District Hospital Credianus Mgimba said the infected persons died between Fri 30 Oct 2015 and Sat 31 Oct 2015 and were from Segera, Kwamnele, Kwengoma, Kwamatuku and Ndolwa. Mgimba explained that they have set up a special camp for the infected at Ndolwa, Kwamkono, Segera, Kwamatuku and Kwamnele wards as well as another camp at Kivesa in Handeni.

Mgimba said education on preventive measures is provided to wananchi, who were also educated about giving prompt information if they saw anyone suffering from the disease around their areas.

